                <note rend="inline" type="source">875.01/259: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Albania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tirana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-01-08T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 8, 1925—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 9—10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. The Italian Government will withhold recognition from the Government of Ahmed
                    Zogu even though it may fulfill constitutional forms but will await
                    developments. My Italian colleague, who informs me of this, had offered the
                    contrary advice. French, British, Servian and Greek representatives seem to
                    anticipate no difficulties will be raised by their Government[s]. Ahmed Bey has
                    assumed portfolio of Ministry of Foreign Affairs ad interim. Constituent <pb
                        facs="0616" n="490" xml:id="pg_490"/> Assembly adjourned last May reconvened
                    for January 15th to regularise new regime.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
